episodes.title: Episode #99: THE FLU SUCKS! Shooting a pilot in NYC, loud chewers on the train, meningitis and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode, sick in a hotel room in bed, I talk about what it was like the time I thought I had the flu but it was meningitis. Plus, I talk about the pilot I'm shooting in NYC, how a slight change in attitude has already made 2017 better than 2016, why I eat like an animal and more, more, more.

episodes.title: Episode #98: A special Valentine's episode with me and the wifey in bed like John a
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this special Valentine's Day episode of "Fairly Normal" my wife, Bethany, joins me. We answer your questions about love and relationships while laying in bed like John and Yoko. What is the one thing that bothers us the most about the other, how we solve problems, my favorite thing about her and a TON more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #97: Singing Kelly Clarkson w the windows down, THE SUPER BOWL, talking to germaphobes..
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Episode #97: I talk about forgetting my windows were down and getting caught singing Kelly Clarkson at the top of my lungs at a stoplight, THE SUPER BOWL, why people hate Tom Brady, why talking to germaphobes is a bad idea and a more!!

episodes.title: Episode #96: Battling your demons, putting a value on yourself, fuck censorship and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode I talk about having to battle my demons over the last 10 days or so, the importance of putting a value on yourself, legalizing prostitution, fuck censorship and I have a guaranteed way for you to make a TON of money but you have to hurry. Plus...more, more and more.

episodes.title: Episode #95: Gambling, not letting fear beat you, fuck parenting books and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode I talk about how parenting books can do more harm than good, gambling, somebody who stood way too close to me in an empty elevator, not letting fear control you and a TON MORE. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #94: Tait Fletcher, actor, entrepreneur, mixed martial artist, inspirational guy joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Tait Fletcher, actor, entrepreneur, mixed martial artist and inspirational guy joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. He talks about selling drugs at 12, when he realized he needed to get his shit together, how he got started acting, his first stunt (insanity), he drops a TON of inspiration all over this episode and more! Definitely check this one out!

episodes.title: Episode #93: Ben Greenfield, fitness guru, stops by & BLOWS ME AWAY w/ his knowledge. A must listen.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Ben Greenfield, health/fitness guru, joins Josh on this episode of "Fairly Normal." His wealth of knowledge about exercise, diet and overall well being is astounding! A MUST listen for anyone looking to get in shape, to find alternative healthy snacks, he debunks some massive myths, shares the one thing that none of us are doing that we all should to be healthier that and a TON MORE! You have to check this one out.

episodes.title: Episode #92: My wife! I admit things to her for the 1st time, why we like each other & more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Episode #92: My wife!!! I thought we should start 2017 off with the beautiful Bethany Ashton Wolf. We admit things for the first time, talk about the first impression we had of each other, her movie and her journey to get where she is, why we still like each other and more! and, YES, she actually is this nice. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #91: ME! Why Steve Martin's tweet to Carrie Fisher was ok, advice to step parents and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Episode #91 is ME! Late night, post show in my hotel room after one or two drinks and an edible. These are always my favorite ones where I answer your questions and also some of my own. I talk about why I think the uproar over Steve Martin's tweet is out of control, I give a little advice to step parents, my second book, how to stay positive and more. Let's go.

episodes.title: Episode #90: ME! After one too many tequila shots answering your questions in my hotel room
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode it's ME...after one too many tequila shots, answering your questions in my hotel room while eating Cheezits. I'm too scared to listen but you shouldn't be.

episodes.title: Episode #90: Billy Wayne Davis, touring w Sturgill Simpson, growing up small town & Mitch Hedberg
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: The very funny Billy Wayne Davis joins me on this episode. If you don't know Billy Wayne you have to check this out. His tone and cadence alone make me laugh not to mention that he's smart and the exact opposite of what you'd expect him to be. We talk touring with Sturgill Simpson, Mitch Hedberg, growing up in a small town and a ton more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #89: Steve Simeone, we compare heckler stories, who we would be on the A-team and positivity
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Steve Simeone joins me on this episode of "Fairly Normal." We compare our favorite heckler stories, talk about which character we would want to be from the A-Team, the benefits of choosing to stay positive and a ton more. PLEASE listen to the end of this one. Inspiration a plenty. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #88: This "Fairly Normal" is an ep of "Good Call", a show I do w/ Adam Ray. Check it out.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: This "Fairly Normal" is actually an episode of "Good Call", which is a podcast I do with my buddy Adam Ray. Trust me. Give it a shot. Jokes, impersonations, top 5 lists, songs that made me cry, oh and we also mix in some sports. Listen and then find "Good Call' on iTunes.

episodes.title: Episode #87: ME! Talking Top 5 burger joints, asshole little dogs, movie critics and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" I talk about asshole little dogs, my top 5 burger places, I answer your questions from Twitter, what I would do if I saw a bear, Beth joins for a few seconds and more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #86: ME! Worst sides at Thanksgiving, Turkey Day etiquette, Kanye, your ?s & more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another solocast and I LOVE DOING THESE! Today I covered Thanksgiving Do's and Don'ts, the worst side dishes, Kanye, another pet peeve, what somebody possibly taking away legal weed made me realize about myself, I answer your Twitter questions and I get kinda heated with myself. That and a TON more! Check it out!

episodes.title: Episode #86: ME! Worst sides at Thanksgiving, Turkey Day etiquette, Kanye, answer your ?s & more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another solocast and I LOVE DOING THESE! Today I covered Thanksgiving Do's and Don'ts, the worst side dishes, Kanye, another pet peeve, what somebody possibly taking away legal weed made me realize about myself, I answer your Twitter questions and I get kinda heated with myself. That and a TON more! Check it out!

episodes.title: Episode #85: Brody Stevens, my long time friend and I get into unexpected waters. It's a good one.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Brody Stevens joins me on this episode. Brody and I have known each other for so long you can hear me call him Steve a few times! I thought this episode was going to get into the Cubs and his journey with them this postseason and, well, we definitely took an unexpected turn. Great guy. VERY open. We talk about starting comedy at the same time in Seattle together, being uninhibited on stage and then the rabbit hole opens...check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #84: ME! Stories from my single dad years, post-election talk, Pet Peeve of the day & MORE!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: ME! At my house, cooking dinner and telling more stories from my single dad days, what happens AFTER the elections, Pet Peeve of the day, I almost burn my hand clean off (I apologize for the string of swears but not really) and a TON more! Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #83: Dean Delray we talk music, drugs, comedy, diabetes, his motorcycle accident and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Dean Delray joins me on this episode and it is a killer. We talk about his transition from being a musician for 25 years into comedy, his brutal motorcycle accident, diabetes, he introduces me to some AMAZING new music and a ton more. I could have talked to Dean for 2 more hours. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #82: ME! HGH, embarrassing Boomer, a cultural appropriation update and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Episode #82 is ME! Another solocast...I talk about an argument that my son and I got into and the lesson I learned from it, thinking about taking HGH and hormones, I have an update on the cultural appropriation talk  from last podcast, my friend Heather McDonald and her big news, another pet peeve and a ton more! check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #81: ME! I try to figure out what cultural appropriation is and a ton more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: ME! Another solocast....I talk about my time as a single dad (and why I don't talk about the bad parts of those days too much), I try to figure out exactly what cultural appropriation is, my newest favorite musician, my pet peeve of the day and much more! Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #80: ME! Talking about my special, the best scare in the world and more
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: ME! Another solocast from my house. Today I talk about getting my special together, how the "slow stroll" in front of my car is one of my biggest pet peeves, not wanting to develop old man ass, accidentally getting gum in a girl's pubes and a ton more. Check it out, check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #79: Jay Larson, comedian, writer and actor joins Josh on this episode
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Jay Larson, comedian, writer and actor, joins Josh on this episode as they talk about Big Papi retiring, Jay finding a room of dick sculptures in his dad's house after he passed, being a sponge as a young comic and a TON more! Dude is super fucking funny. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #78: ME!! Back from Oldchella I talk about the bands and taking mushrooms
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" it's ME and I'm back from Oldchella. What a great fucking weekend! I review every band, talk about taking mushrooms and the importance of making memories. Hope you like it.

episodes.title: Episode #77: ME! Talking about people walking out of my show, exciting podcast news and more!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" it's ME! I talk about figuring out my new special, having people walk out of my shows offended this weekend, trying to decide if I should do mushrooms at Oldchella, why I don't want to get old and a ton more! Check. It. Out.

episodes.title: Episode #76: ME...talking food poisoning, the debate and a bunch of silly shit
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another solocast from the Casa del Wolf. I talk about my weekend bout with food poisoning, the death of Jose Fernandez and the last half is filled with my take on the debate. Plus, lots and lots of the usual tangents. Loving these solocasts more and more! Spread the word.

episodes.title: Episode #75: Steve Kazee, Tony Award winner, actor, singer joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Steve Kazee, actor, singer and Tony Award winner joins Josh on this episode and they run the gamut on emotions for sure. Steve talks about having to perform a song from "Once" LIVE on the Today Show right after learning that his mom was passing (the whole story, including how he got through his opening night, is AMAZING), his talks his love for WWE, Josh tells a story about a girl whose bellybutton looked like a cat's ahole and MORE! See? The whole gamut. This ep is a must on many levels.

episodes.title: Episode #74: ME! A big work announcement and a ton more!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: ME! Another solocast! I love doing these so much and this one made me laugh out loud to myself a few times! I share some cool work news about a TV show I'll be on, football is back, I sat next to one of my biggest pet peeves of all-time on the plane (and I didn't kill him), I talk about conquering a huge fear AND I came up with the best name for an R&B group ever. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #73: Coy Bowles, guitarist/keyboard player/song writer from the Zac Brown Band joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Coy Bowles, guitar player/keyboardist/song writer, from the Zac Brown Band joins Josh on Fairly Normal. They talk about how the ZBB got together, Coy tells a few insane stories from the road, where his favorite place to play is, what it was like for him growing up in a small town in Georgia and he shares something about performing that he's never told anyone before. This episode is PACKED with great stories that take you behind the velvet rope. If you like music, this one is for you.

episodes.title: Episode #72: ME! I think I'm starting to figure out how to soocast! My best one yet
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" it's ME and I think I'm starting to figure out how to solocast. I really want to be able to do entertaining solocasts but I was really nervous doing them at first. This one is my best. Not perfect yet but getting way better. I talk about people being self-involved, doing nice shit for people, Colin Kaepernick and I improv three songs that should instantly go to #1 on the charts. Check it out!

episodes.title: Episode #71: Kevin Clancy (KFC), from Barstool Sports joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Kevin Clancy (KFC), from Barstool Sports, joins Josh on this episode of "Fairly Normal." This episode covers a little bit of everything. They discuss if blind people are part of an elaborate hoax, if Helen Keller was faking it, which sport has the funniest athletes and Josh asks Kevin a list of questions that Josh thinks will help determine right away if he is going to like someone. This ep has a ton of laughs. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #70: ME....way too high. I apologize in advance.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of Fairly Normal, it's just me and I'm way too high. I answer your questions....kinda. Pay no attention to the long pauses or the chunks where I'm clearly talking to myself. This is a mess but I promised I would put it out. Here ya go....P.S. didn't express my opinion on the Kaepernick situation as well as i would have liked. I'll get to that on today's podcast.

episodes.title: Episode #69: Josh Adam Meyers, comedian and creator of the God Damn Comedy Jam joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Josh Adam Meyers, comedian and creator of the God Damn Comedy Jam joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. The Comedy Jam is my favorite live show in Los Angeles that is now a show on Comedy Central! Josh talks about never giving up on his dream, addiction, why comedy songs don't need to rhyme and how he persevered through the death of his best friend. Some very funny and very heavy shit on this episode. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #68: Boomer and The Old Man! Fresh from the Zac Brown concert at Fenway
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Boomer and The Old Man are back! We recorded this on a train from Boston to Maine the morning after we saw Zac Brown at Fenway Park. We review the concert (which was AMAZING), Jacob tells me why he thinks his generation doesn't love Rock-n-Roll and I continue to have more old man moments. Uh-oh. That and a ton more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #67:  Another brother! Dan Wolf, joins me on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of Fairly Normal one of my other brothers, Dan, joins me at the Casa De Wolf to shoot the shit. We tell embarrassing childhood stories, he talks about his battle with depression (I definitely heard some shit I had never heard before!), he says that he heard when I described him as the "auschwitzy" version of me and MUCH more. Good stuff.

episodes.title: Episode #66: Freddie Prinze Jr. joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Freddie Prinze Jr. joins Josh on a crazy episode of "Fairly Normal." I love stories about old Hollywood and he has the best ones I've heard. He talks about the time his dad sparred with Muhammad Ali and a great story about his dad being at Richard Pryor's house. He also talks about how he coped with his father's suicide, how it affected him and how he came out the other side. A great story about Chuck Norris breaking his rib, too! So many great bits on this episode. A MUST LISTEN. On a sidenote, the calmest, most down to earth dude I have met in this town. He gets it. Good stuff.

episodes.title: Episode #65: Alison Rosen, podcaster and host, joins Josh on this episode
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Alison Rosen, podcaster and host, joins Josh on this episode of "Fairly Normal." We talk about her being pregnant, what she will take from her parents' style of raising kids and what she won't, one of her biggest regrets and MUCH, MUCH MORE. This one could have gone on for another 2 hours. Check it out, check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #64: Boomer and the Old Man are back!!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" Jacob Wolf is back for another edition of "Boomer and The Old Man." We talk about his weekend as the batboy for the Red Sox, if he worries about me and a TON more. We crammed a bunch into this one!! Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #63: ME...definitely the most personal one yet. Hope you like it.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: A solocast where I discuss the recent death of one of my heroes. A friend of mine that I went to college with passed. Wrestled with putting this out but it was very cathartic for me and, ultimately, decided to post it just in case it could help someone else someday. Be good to each other. Josh

episodes.title: Episode #62: Jeremiah Watkins, comedian and improv king, joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: You might not know him now but in a few years everybody will know Jeremiah Watkins. A very funny comedian who can be seen on The Roast Battle, The God Damn Comedy Jam and Kill Tony. On this episode we discuss why there hasn't been a Fat Albert porn, what makes somebody good at improv, being bullied in school and how that shaped his comedy and much more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #61: Jessimae Peluso, comedian, stops by the Casa del Wolf for a podcast
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode, Jessimae Peluso, comedian and funny motherfucker, joins Josh at the Casa Del Wolf. The two of them may or may not have had a smidge to smoke and they get into Bigfoot, ghost stories, the epiphany that Jessimae had that has changed the way she looks at herself in the world and a whole lot more. This one gets a gold star for sure.

episodes.title: Episode #60: Sarah Colonna, comedian and one of my favorite people in the world, joins me
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Sarah Colonna, comedian and one of my favorite people ever, is my guest on this episode of "Fairly Normal." We talk about her recent wedding, the time she got drunk and left flowers at someone's door to apologize, her Carrie Underwood sighting and at the end, her husband, Jon Ryan sits in for a few minutes. Good time had by all. Check it out!

episodes.title: Episode #59: Sarah Tiana is my guest. See if you can guess which one of us is high. Yikes.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal" the hilarious, Sarah Tiana, joins me. We taped this in my hotel room after we shot an episode of "Comedy Knockout" for TruTv. See if you can guess which one of us is high. Yikes. She tells me about her new TV show, why she is a huge sports fan and I can't remember what else because ONE OF US was a little toasty. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #58: Paul de Gelder, shark attack survivor and conservationist joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of "Fairly Normal", my buddy, shark attack survivor, conservationist and all around bad ass, Paul de Gelder joins me. We talk about the shark attack that changed his life, the moment in the hospital he stopped feeling sorry for himself, three simple steps we ALL can do to help the planet and MUCH, much more. Truly inspirational shit. Don't miss it.

episodes.title: Episode #57: Boomer and The Old Man
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Boomer and The Old Man are back and this episode gets kinda deep. Josh tells Jacob that he's been worried about him lately and why he's been worried, they talk about Jacob moving out, going to Fenway next week and a ton more. Josh fights back tears a bit on this one. Do not miss it!

episodes.title: Episode #56: Brandi Glanville, author and reality TV star joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Brandi Glanville, author and reality TV star, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about what it was really like for Brandi on "Real Housewives", if she has any regrets, orgies and what she needs in a man. If you know anything about Brandi, you know that she has no filter and not one fuck to give. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #55: Sam Tripoli, comedian and the most unfiltered man in the world joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Sam Tripoli, comedian and the most unfiltered, honest person ever to be in the studio, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about Sam's coke addiction, why college students need to toughen up a bit, Sam's tells us what sex move he was doing before it was cool and a ton of stories about doing comedy in LA. That and much, much more. Check. It. Out.

episodes.title: Episode #54: Boomer and The Old Man return
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Josh's son, Jacob, is back for their weekly edition of "Boomer and The Old Man." They talk about what Jacob considers to be my strengths and weaknesses as a parent, Beth (my wife) being away this summer, how my brain wasn't working, my voice modulation problems and much, much more. Check it out

episodes.title: Episode #53: Mo Mandel, comedian and producer, joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Mo Mandel, comedian, joins Josh to lend his completely unfiltered sense of humor to this episode of Fairly Normal. He talks about swimming with Great White sharks, wrestling a 103 pound Asian girl in HS, the complaint that all of his GFs have about him and much, much more! One of the funniest episodes yet.

episodes.title: Episode #52: Boomer and The Old Man return
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Boomer and The Old Man return on this episode of Fairly Normal! Josh asks Jacob about his trip to London, they talk about their worst throw up stories and what alcohol they can't drink because of it, Josh has a true old man moment and they share a nice Father's Day moment. That and much, much more.

episodes.title: Episode 51: DJ Laura Lux, entertainer, DJ and model, joins Josh on this episode
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: DJ Laura Lux, entertainer, DJ and model joins Josh on this episode of "Fairly Normal." They talk about how she started shaming guys who sent her unwarranted dick pics on social media and how that went viral, what it was like growing up in Australia in a town of 50 people, why In-n-Out is the best burger, why she might be a fuckboi and MUCH MORE!

episodes.title: Episode #50: Dani Mathers, 2015 Playmate of the Year and Marijuana advocate, joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Dani Mathers, 2015 Playmate of the Year, Marijuana advocate and actress, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about weed, threesomes and the how she got her audition for Playboy. Lots of good stuff on this one!

episodes.title: Episode #49: The return of Boomer and The Old Man
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Josh's son, Jacob, sits with Josh for the triumphant return of "Boomer and The Old Man." Josh and Jacob's special bond is on full display during this episode as they talk about being on #TEAMGOSLING, Jacob's upcoming trip to London, they compare their horrible English accents and Josh tells Jacob why he let him put his finger in a socket when he was a kid.

episodes.title: Episode #48: Nick Swardson, comedian, writer and actor joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Nick Swardson, actor, comedian and writer joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. Nick talks about letting squirrels walk all over him, what Prince meant to the people of Minnesota, his extreme style of comedy and much, much more. Dude is hysterical. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #47: Owen Benjamin, comedian and actor, joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Owen Benjamin, comedian and actor, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about how his newborn has changed how he views his free time  and his masturbation rituals, why people not giving you shit is an insult and they improv the most ridiculous song of all-time. That and much, much more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #46: Greg Fitzsimmons, comedian, writer and funny motherfucker joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Greg Fitzsimmons, comedian, writer, host and funny motherfucker joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about some deep shit, some funny shit and they also just talk shit. Greg is one of the smartest, funniest dudes out there. Definitely check this one out.

episodes.title: Episode #45: Ben Gleib, comedian, host and modern day philosopher joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Ben Gleib, comedian, host and modern day philosopher, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They may or may not have smoked a wee bit too much weed so to try and describe everything they talked about...not easy. Ben shares how he trained his brain not to feel cold, he unleashes his rap skills and tells a crazy story about his grandfather in the Holocaust. For sure a  can't miss episode.

episodes.title: Episode #44: Josh Hopkins, actor and handsome motherfucker, joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Josh Hopkins, actor, from "Quantico", "Cougar Town" and a ton of other stuff joins Josh on this episode of "Fairly Normal." They talk about Josh's audition he did WITH Tom Cruise for "Jerry Maquire", his love of Kentucky basketball, why he started running triathlons and a TON more. Josh is really, really funny. Gotta check this one out.

episodes.title: Episode #43: Jenny Johnson,  the hilarious comedian and writer, joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Jenny Johnson, the incredibly funny comedian and writer, joins Josh to talk about embarrassing high school stories, stalkers and how the death of her father affected her writing and comedy. That and much, much more!

episodes.title: Episode #42: The incredibly funny, Tom Segura, joins Josh for this episode
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Tom Segura, one of the funniest and most successful comedians out there right now, joins Josh to talk about why Woody Allen is unfortunately getting a free pass, he tells a frightening/hysterical story about living near a crack park and he also discusses what affect being in a coma had on him. Great stuff from this incredibly funny guy. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #41: Carrie Keagan, actress, host and funny motherfucker joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Carrie Keagan, actress, hostess and funny motherfucker joins Josh for this completely uncensored, nothing off-limits, episode of Fairly Normal. The play a ridiculous game of "What's Grosser?", talk about if girls with big booty's are taken more seriously than girls with big boobs, how was the first to bring "uncensored" to celebrity interviews and MUCH MORE! Don't miss this one.

episodes.title: Episode #40: Margaret Cho, Comedian, activist and all around bad ass joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Margaret Cho, comedian, activist and all around bad ass, joins Josh on this episode. And, as a bonus, the very funny Scott Silverman sits in as well. They talk about Mitch Helberg, animal ghosts, the incredible crush Josh had on Margaret and (because of the copious amount of weed smoked) a TON MORE that I can't remember! She is the absolute best. Don't miss this one.

episodes.title: Episode #39: Tony Hinchcliffe, comedian, writer and one of the future stars of comedy
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Tony Hinchcliffe, comedian, writer and one of the future stars of comedy, joins Josh for Fairly Normal. NOTHING is off limits with Tony as they talk about about Larry Wilmore using the "N" word, how much Tony enjoys pushing the envelope with his comedy, growing up in a rough neighborhood and much, much more. Plus, Josh goes on an angry rant at the top of the show.

episodes.title: Episode #38: ME! A solocast where I answer your questions and admit some shit!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: The guest on this episode is ME! I talk about the importance of music in my life, I admit some stuff to myself, I answer all of your questions, I do all of my amazing impressions and much, much more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #37: Taryn Southern, internet sensation, singer, actress joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Taryn Southern (internet sensation, actress, singer)joins Josh on this episode to talk about the big break up that changed her life, her traumatic experience on American Idol, what her ideal man is, the difference between Prince and Michael Jackson and more!

episodes.title: Episode #36: Graham Elwood, comedian and documentarian, joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Graham Elwood, comedian and documentarian, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about Graham's divorce and how he bounced back from it, ridiculous stories from the road, the documentary he made about his trips to Afghanistan, they invent a sex move called "The Hot Corner" and much, much more. Might be the funniest one yet. Check it out!

episodes.title: Episode #35: My brother, Jonathan Wolf, Part 2! We hear what happened in jail
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: My brother, Jonathan, sits down for part 2 of our interview. He talks about what his time was like in jail, how it changed him and he shares a few embarrassing stories about me from my childhood. He brings the heat again.

episodes.title: Episode #34: Jenn Sterger, writer, comedian and huge sports fan, joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Jenn Sterger, writer/comedian joins Josh to talk about how an unsolicited workplace dick pic, not only got her fired but also changed the course of her life. This episode also has THE GREATEST ending to any podcast ever. Don't want to give it away but...wow. Don't miss this one!

episodes.title: Episode #33: Jonathan Wolf, my brother, delivers the best one yet
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: My brother, Jonathan, sits in and delivers the best episode yet. It was so good the batteries ran out and we will have to do a part 2! We talk about how he walked away from an engineering degree being only ONE CLASS SHORT, our childhood and why he ended up in jail for 80 days. GOTTA CHECK THIS ONE OUT!

episodes.title: Episode #32: Brendan Schaub, fighter/ podcast host/actor joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Brendan Schaub, fighter/podcast host/actor, joins Josh on this episode. Brendan talks about being a new father, the one part of himself that he hopes his son doesn't get, how his brother hit him with a brick and a golf club growing up, why he got out of professional fighting and much, much more. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #31: Carly Kuhn, the one and only Cartorialist, joins me!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Carly Kuhn, The Cartorialist, joins Josh on Fairly Normal. She talks about her mercurial, completely unorthodox rise in the art world, what her big break was, her "go to" karaoke songs and much, much more! A great story of chasing your dreams and finding new ones!

episodes.title: Episode #30: Thai Rivera, comedian and Trump supporter stops in for a spirited coversation
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Comedian, and Trump supporter, Thai Rivera talks to Josh about what it is about Trump he likes so much, why (as a Mexican-American) he supports the Donald, what it was like telling his parents he was gay, the importance of standing up for yourself and his very specific views on feminism. This one is a doozy!

episodes.title: Episode #29: Jen Widerstrom,  trainer from "Biggest Loser", joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Jen Widerstrom, trainer from the "Biggest Loser" joins Josh on this motivational episode. Josh finally tells what his big health scare was, Jen discusses motivation, where it comes from and how to harness it, how being healthy is not as daunting as it sounds and Josh and Jen unveil their big fitness opportunity for everyone. Plus Jen answers your questions! Tune in!

episodes.title: Episode #28: Brian Redban, comedian and podcast pioneer, joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Brian Redban, comedian and one of the originators of Deathsquad.TV, joins Josh to talk about the early days of podcasting, how he and Joe Rogan found their way to it, what he thinks is "next", if Bigfoot is real, are we all just living in a giant SIM, how a tough year led him down a dark, dark road and much more!

episodes.title: Episode #27: ME! Another solocast from my living room!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another "Fairly Normal" solocast with just ME! I love doing these. Unfortunately, I started to run out of batteries so I had to cut it a little short but I did get to all of your questions plus, I got a chance to give my two cents about the embarrassing state of politics in America right now and Bethany walks by in the middle of the podcast to show me her booty. What a beautiful day indeed.

episodes.title: Episode #26: Sex therapist, Simone Bienne, joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Sex therapist, Simone Bienne, joins Josh on this episode and they talk about EVERYTHING. Simone talks about her past abusive relationships and how they shaped her and her work, they dissect Josh's sex life, they answer all of your questions and much, much more. Truly an eye opening episode!

episodes.title: Episode #25: My daughter, Kaitlynn, joins me for a podcast at my house
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: My daughter, Kaitlynn, joins me on a very special episode of "Fairly Normal." We talk about one of my least favorite topics...guys that she has dated; plus, her job at the pet hospital, her dreams and much, much more. Check out this episode with my baby girl.

episodes.title: Episode #24: Clifton Collins Jr. graces the studios with his amazing stories
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Clifton Collins Jr sits with Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal and shares some AMAZING stories. Clifton has been in "Traffic", "TigerLand", "Babel", "Capote" and literally 100 other movies and TV shows. He shares how Samuel Jackson helped shape him as an actor, talks about how his father's suicide affected him, what it was like running away from home, his book called "Prison Ramen" and TONS more. Don't miss this one!

episodes.title: Episode #23: ME! Another solocast but this one is from San Francisco
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another Solocast on this episode of "Fairly Normal' but this one is done in the wee hours of the morning from my hotel room in San Francisco. I answer all of the questions you posted for me online plus I get a little deeper than I was expecting. Check that; a lot deeper. Hope you like it because I love doing them.

episodes.title: Episode #22: My wife spills the beans
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: My wife joins me on tonight's special Valentine's Day edition of Fairly Normal. We covered a TON of ground...We answered all of your questions, told the story about how Beth used to sleep in my closet, we reenacted a scene from Ghost and much, much more. Best one yet.

episodes.title: Episode #21: ME! Another solo podcast!
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Another solo episode of "Fairly Normal!" On this episode I answer your questions from online again and we get into who my biggest inspirations are, the enormous realization I had about myself and how it is going to affect my comedy, the unfortunate way I used to put my kids to sleep and much, much more! I love doing these solocasts! Don't miss it!!

episodes.title: Episode #20: ME! I do a solocast from my house. Definitely different and definitely fun.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Today's guest is me! I talk about, well, just about everything. I answer all of your questions that you left on my Facebook page; my biggest regret, what was the lowest point in my life and how did I get past it, I tell some Joey Diaz stories and lots, lots more. Plus, someone knocks on my front door mid podcast. This is a guaranteed good time.

episodes.title: Episode #19: Marilu Henner from Taxi, Evening Shade and best selling author joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Actress and best selling author, Marilu Henner, joins Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal. She tells some amazing Andy Kaufman stories, talks about how Danny Devito got his role on "Taxi", she discusses how the death of her parents affected her and MUCH, MUCH MORE! Do not miss this one.

episodes.title: Episode #18: Sherry Thomas, casting director for Walking Dead, Breaking Bad and ton of other stuff
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Sherry Thomas, the casting director for Walking Dead, Breaking Bad a TON of other stuff talks about what it was like casting those two shows, the benefits of casting a show that is not filled with stars, the story about her getting me my SAG card way back when and our very, very uncomfortable first Thanksgiving together. Oh, did I mention we grew up next to each other? Don't miss it!

episodes.title: Episode #17: Tim Omundson from Galavant, Psych, Deadwood and tons of other stuff joins Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Tim Omundson from "Galavant", "Psych", "Deadwood" and a ton of other shows joins Josh to talk about why Galavant is the most fun he's ever had as an actor, when and how he started taking charge in the audition room, the power of believing and much, much more.

episodes.title: Episode #16: Clay Travis, one of the most controversial people in sports, sits with me
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Clay Travis, one of the most controversial people in sports, sits with me for a few hours. We talk about the moment he knew that having a strong opinion was the most important thing in his line of business, how brutal sports fans can be, why he doesn't like to wear pants and much, much more!

episodes.title: Episode #15: Kevin Youkilis sits with Josh on this episode of Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Red Sox great, Kevin Youkilis, joins me to talk about being told he was never going to make it and how that drove him during his career, tearing up during his last game at Fenway, what it's like not to be the best athlete at family reunions (Tom Brady is his brother in-law) and just a TON of great stories! Baseball and lots, lots more.

episodes.title: Episode #14 Bryan Callen sits with Josh to talk about, well, everything.
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Bryan Callen sits down with Josh to talk about his thirst for knowledge, getting started/rejected in Hollywood and bouncing back AND how he wants his kids to remember him. Plus, so much more. Definitely the most well rounded podcast yet!

episodes.title: Episode #13: Me and my son do a podcast from my home office
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Josh talks about Odell Beckham Jr, kids having sex with their teachers and then his son Jacob joins him to sing a song and talks some shit to each other.

episodes.title: Episode #12: Chelsea Lately Reunion - Jo Koy, Heather McDonald and Chris Franjola join Josh
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Jo Koy, Heather McDonald and Chris Franjola join Josh to talk about their experiences on Chelsea Lately -- the good, the bad, what their favorite experiences were and how the show changed their lives. Good, good stuff. Check it out.

episodes.title: Episode #11: Drama from Young and Reckless joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Drama, from Y&R, sits down with Josh and talks about being in a coma, how he started his business, wanting to get into podcasting and a lot more. Very inspirational guy. Don't miss this one.

episodes.title: Episode #9: Bert Kreischer joins Josh on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: The one and only, Bert Kreischer, tells some amazing stories on this episode of "Fairly Normal." From robbing a train in Russia to the single funniest child/dog story of all-time. This is an episode you can not miss.

episodes.title: Episode #9: Haley Reinhart joins me on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: The amazingly talented singer/songwriter, Haley Reinhart, joins Josh and talks about how it was singing in a band with her mom and dad as a kid, getting cast in Bill Burr's new animated series on Netflix and what her favorite vocal track is of all-time.

episodes.title: Episode #8: My Parents join me on Fairly Normal
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: My parents join me on this episode of Fairly Normal. They talk about what they think the worst thing I did growing up was, what they thought of me getting into comedy and what they think is the most important thing a parent can do for their kid.

episodes.title: Episode #7: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf with special guest Tiffany Haddish
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode Josh talks with comedian/actress Tiffany Haddish. This is the the funniest episode yet. Tiffany has some crazy stories but her story about how she got here and what she had to overcome is amazing. Do not miss this one!

episodes.title: Episode #6: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf with guest Olympic boxer Tony Jeffries
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of Fairly Normal Tony tells Josh how many times he's been punched in the face and the number is crazy! They also admit something that neither one of them has ever admitted before. Some amazing stories in this one. Don't miss it.

episodes.title: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf: Episode #5 w/ guest Angie Stevenson
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode, Josh talks to model/actress, Angie Stevenson, about how she got into the business, the best vocals from any song ever, plus, I play the song that I sold to a movie. Boom.

episodes.title: Ep #4: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf: Guest Jacob Wolf
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode Josh talks to his son Jacob a month before he leaves for college. This was the VERY FIRST podcast. It even had a different name. Josh calls it "Lifted w/ Josh Wolf." A great hour spent with one of the truly unique father/son relationships out there.

episodes.title: Episode #3: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf - Guest Radio Legend Frank Kramer
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode Josh talks with radio legend Frank Kramer about how podcasts have changed radio, the "all in" move he made that catapulted his career and how he didn't know he had a daughter until she was 5. Don't miss this one!!

episodes.title: Episode #2: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf - Ross Mathews
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: On this episode of Fairly Normal, Josh and Ross are back together. The two talk about what it's like to regroup after your dream gig goes away, they reminisce about their old podcast and Ross does his best dirty talk.

episodes.title: Episode #1: Fairly Normal w/ Josh Wolf - Greg Garcia
episodes.author: Josh Wolf
episodes.summary: Episode One of "Fairly Normal" and Josh sits down with "My Name is Earl" and "Raising Hope" creator Greg Garcia. They talk about casting, staying true to your vision and Ambien.
